            <thetext>We hit this bug with IE9 there is no problem with FF. We&#39;ve not testet other IE versions.

If the focus is in an input field (like TextField,...) and the user tries to remove the value with the backspace key the browser loades the last visited website.

One possible workaround since the bug is fixed, is adding a listener to the input field and call event.preventDefault() if the field is read-only and keyIdentifier equals &quot;Backspace&quot;.

Regards,
Andreas</thetext>
